node.text:
Stuart demonstrates exactly how to use a HAIMER Presetter to get offsets. This can be done while the CNC Machine is cutting chips and making money. When the machine is ready to change jobs, you simply load the new tools, while all offsets are transferred to the machine automatically. This allows for a much shorter set up time and keeps the CNC Machine making money.

node.text:
Ceramic tooling is highly efficient when it comes to CNC machining Inconel and other nickel based super alloys…

Ceramics are also known for their fireworks show… meaning they are always ran dry and turn into a ball of flames as they engage the material. Don’t be alarmed though as ceramics are chemically inert. The tool material does not heat up at all and instead dispels the heat from the cut.

Although Ceramics run faster than carbide tools, their life span in cut is considerably less. Companies that have a ton of Inconel to machine should be using ceramics… but trust me, there is a science involved. Pro-Tip: Many use tool management in the CNC to run efficiently… meaning they will load 5 endmills at a time and give each a life expectancy… and then each tool runs right after the last to get the necessary material removal.
